    • Constructor Detail

      • AbstractMessageAwareFiller

        protected AbstractMessageAwareFiller(PropertyResolver resolver,
                                     Map<String,List<String>> aliases,
                                     Class<M> messageType)
        The list of properties is indexed by an alias that is known by the implementation. For example, if the keys is defined like this: 
         Map<String, List<String>> keys = new HashMap<>();
 keys.put("to", Arrays.asList("ogham.email.to"));
 keys.put("from", Arrays.asList("ogham.email.from", "mail.smtp.from"));
        The implementation can then retrieve real property value using map key (alias): 
         getProperty("from");
 // will return either the value of "ogham.email.from" or "mail.smtp.from"
        Parameters:
        resolver - the property resolver used to check property existence and get property values
        aliases - a list of property keys indexed by an alias
        messageType - the class of the message that this implementation can handle
